# VERSION
v0.12.11

# Changelog
- v0.12.11
    - Removed callback ip & port from header of cronjob executor request and set them in meta.
    - Upgraded infra version to v0.16.2
- v0.12.10
    - Adjusted the failure judgement logic in executor: Failed/succeed is determined by response code and msg together.
- v0.12.9
    - Fixed bug of when async task finalized callback but got wrong response code and status.
- v0.12.8
    - Extend callback_time_scanner functionality to a assembled scanner, which support sync/async/progress callback.
    - Sync run stuck config is added.
    - Graceful clean-up is added in new Scanner as well.
- v0.12.7
    - Replaced jenkins deployment and use python as a substitute.
    - Added go mod tidy in tidy_to.sh
- v0.12.6
    - Changed docker compose file to llimit log size.
- v0.12.5
    - Changed infra version to v1.0.0 in go.mod
- v0.12.4
    - Refactored cronjob executor, added callback info in req header.
- v0.12.3
    - Changed Dockerfile
- v0.12.2
    - Removed callback success status for cronjob.
    - Added api for fetching all progress of runs.
- v0.12.1
    - Replaced DeleteKeepRecent with chunked deletion to avoid large data deletion issue.
    - Extended Summary of runs to show statistics by status.
    - Added stats api to show accurate distribution of runs by status.
    - Added non-total progress to show borderless tasks' progress.
    - Added status validation in listRunsByTask / listActiveRuns.
- v0.12.0
    - Added run deletion by trunk rather than hard delete.
    - Added pagination for run list and active runs
    - Removed dry-run for run deletion.
    - Added summary of runs.
- v0.11.0
    - Added configuration for CallbackTimeoutScanner
    - Refactored controller of task mgmt and added run mgmt controller.
    - Move logic of controller to service layer.
    - Added RUN clean up job using date & number of items.
- v0.10.0
    - Supported async task reporting.
    - Added task progress callback.
    - Added periodic task status updater.
- v0.9.1
    - Extend Task List API by adding parameters to filter tasks.
- v0.9.0
    - Added docker build support.
    - Added CI/CD pipeline for cronjob project.
    - Added docker-compose file for deployment.
- v0.8.0
    - Refactored scheduler scan() logic, removed batch fire logic.
    - Added cancel logic in cronjob shutdown.
    - Added json tag in Task/Run model.
    - Added poc project for cronjob.
    - Added limitation for trigger task api.
    - Changed skip type to accurate skip.
    - Set run status to skip immediately once decide skip.
- v0.7.0
    - Redesigned scheduler engine to acquire runnable tasks more accurately.
        - Removed misfired tasks handling from scheduler and datasource.
        - Added overlap handling strategy in scheduler.
        - Added failure handling strategy in scheduler.
        - Added workflow of scan logic in documents.
    - Transitioned table migration in boot by configuration.
- v0.6.0
  - Added Task Service to decouple api and task dao.
  - Added Run Service to decouple api and task dao.
  - Service Task registered.
  - Added mem cache for Enabled Task, query will read from cache first.
  - Scheduler will read from mem cache to get enabled tasks.
- v0.5.0
  - Added task scan strategies on overlap and failure situations.
- v0.4.3
  - Replaced magic strings with constants in all cronjob.
- v0.4.2
  - Replaced  RegisterAutoInferName with registry.RegisterAuto.
- v0.4.1
  - Transitioned run_dao and task_dao to tag-based dependency injection.
  - Updated api by removing manual dependency injection.
  - Use auto reolve in registry_ext/*.go
- v0.4.0
  - Transitioned executor component and shceduler to tag-based dependency injection.
- v0.3.1
  - Added extend runtime dependencies for http server component.
- v0.3.0
  - Transitioned cronjob project to use new infra framework structure.
  - Replaced magic numbers with constants for better code readability.
- v0.2.3 [Unfinished]
  - Runnable version of cronjob using infra framework.
  - HTTP server haven't been transitioned yet.
- v0.2.2 [Unfinished]
  - Transiting cronjob project to infra based project.
- v0.2.1
  - Renamed rr to runDao; renamed tr to taskDao
  - Added comments for cancelMap in Executor
- v0.2.0
  - Changed cronjob DAO to GROM driver.
- v0.1.1
  - Fixed create cronjob api, added fields in TaskDao
  - Added comments for Task & Run models, also updated in README.md
  - Rename *respository to *Dao.
- v0.1.0
  - Initial version of cronjob, it's running
